The Game Store Application is a console-based Java program that simulates a video game store. It allows employees to manage inventory and clients to browse, purchase games, and track their purchase history. The application stores all data in a SQLite database, ensuring persistence of stock and transactions.
Its key features include:
Employee menu - restock games or view all games
Client menu - order games, view available games, or view your previous transactions
Error handling
Database operations to keep track of transactions and stock.

The application uses 5 tables:
Companies(company_id, Name)
Platforms(platform_id, Name)
Games(game_id, title, release_year, company_id)
Junction table Game_Platform(game_id, platform_id, copies_sold, in_stock)
Transactions(transaction_id, game_id, platform_id, client_id, quantity, transaction_type, transaction_date)

