The program begins by asking if the user is a client or an employee. 
Employees can restock games or just view all the games offered by the store, whether in stock or not.
Clients use their id (or generate a new one) to make sure their transactions are private.
They can then buy games, view available games (only in stock), or view their previous transactions.

Methods: 
ProgramStart() - Asks for the role of the user. From here, either EmpMenu() or ClientMenu() are called.
EmpMenu(), ClientMenu() - Provides different options for the user to choose from depending on if they are a client or employee.
RestockScreen() - Allows an employee to restock games.
PurchaseScreen() - Allows clients to buy games.
AvailableScreen(), EmpGameScreen() - Show games and info.
TransactionsScreen() - Shows the client their past transactions.
getUniqueClientId() - Generates an id for new clients and ensures that id is unique.
